The paper deals with reasoning procedures for integrating ontologies and rules, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on Forest Logic Programs (FoLPs), which is a fragment of Answer Set Programming (ASP) that allows for inequality atoms and constants. ASP is a subfield of logic programming (cs.LO) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also introduces f-hybrid knowledge bases, which is a hybrid framework where \SHOQ{} knowledge bases and forest logic programs co-exist. \SHOQ{} is a description logic (DL) that is used in ontology modeling, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
